---

## Impact Assessment

Clearing Windows Security logs can remove evidence of malicious activity and hinder forensic investigations.

---

## Recommended Response

- Preserve all remaining logs.
- Review administrator activity before the log was cleared.
- Investigate process creation and authentication events preceding the action.
- Escalate to the incident response team if the action was unauthorized.

---

## Lessons Learned

Windows Security log clearing is a high-severity event that should always be investigated because attackers commonly use it to conceal malicious actions.
